description.narrative: The number of children 6 to 59 months vaccinated against measles was 1,342,615 (130%). UNICEF procured 8 million measles vaccines and 1,317 measles kits for the medical management of 131,700 children. UNICEF also distributed cholera kits in four affected provinces in addition to Ebola interventions (risk communication and community engagement, infection prevention and control). A scaled-up nutrition response was ensured in 145 health zones which cover 43% of nutrition cluster's priority zones. A total of 436,013 children (49% of UNICEF target and 30% of cluster target) were admitted for treatment of Severe Acute Malnutrition (SAM) during the reporting period. | Status:Met | As-of Date:08/02/2020
